l risks here. If tests use optional Ant integration, maybe I should add Ant? Still, normal coverage wouldn't necessarily require it. If the agent selects AntCompilerAdapter, it might need the optional `org.apache.ant:ant:1.7.1`, which isn’t transitive. I'll ensure we have valid final JSON without Markdown.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra dependency, Docker image, or environment/system property is required. Janino 3.1.0 normally uses the janino artifact plus its transitive commons-compiler dependency; the observed javac failure is caused by a test importing an internal utility package that moved from org.codehaus.janino.util.iterator to org.codehaus.commons.compiler.util.iterator in 3.1.0, not by missing setup.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Existing tests that reference org.codehaus.janino.util.iterator.* must be updated or avoided for 3.1.0 because those utilities now live under org.codehaus.commons.compiler.util.iterator.* in the transitive commons-compiler artifact.\",\n    \"Janino has an optional provided Ant integration dependency; only tests that intentionally exercise AntCompilerAdapter would need Ant, and that is not required for meaningful coverage of normal Janino compiler/evaluator APIs.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0882413dbcb82ae3016a425e29b4088196bb0c58a87deacd7d\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 810, "output": 1050, "cacheRead": 23040, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24900, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782734362095, "responseId": "resp_0882413dbcb82ae3016a425e1a95988196bbabd2ec58f18224"}}
